<subSubSection id="11BB6561DF3CFFA48BF5FE5FBB23F36E" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="591E36EADF3CFFA48BF5FE5FB96EF092" blockId="7.[151,1437,253,1286]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="6BD5EAF8DF3CFFA48BF5FE5FBB4CF0D9" bold="true" box="[199,314,397,422]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Apical flagellomere white, only slightly brown tinged basally, body mostly covered with dense golden rusty pile, calypter with whitish and blackish marginal fringe. Wing brownish infuscated, with a broad, transverse yellow band including large part of discal cell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="591E36EADF3CFFA48BA5FE2BBB23F36E" blockId="7.[151,1437,253,1286]" box="[151,341,505,529]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
